                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2607.00666/2607.00666v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:One-shot VLA adaptation under environmental shifts.Environmental shifts can cause a source-trained VLA policy to fail in the novel target domain.\n(a) Full-data fine-tuning adapts successfully but requires task-wise demonstrations, incurring expensive data collection costs.\n(b) One-shot fine-tuning is data-light but often fails to adapt across tasks.\n(c) Our one-shot adaptation extracts domain-specific directions from fine-tuned weights and adapts the policy via weight arithmetic.",
                "position": 405
            }
